WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.464
The water on

00:00:01.464 --> 00:00:02.928
Earth is millions

00:00:02.928 --> 00:00:04.392
of years old.

00:00:04.392 --> 00:00:05.857
It is constantly

00:00:05.857 --> 00:00:07.321
recycling in a

00:00:07.321 --> 00:00:08.785
loop called the

00:00:08.785 --> 00:00:10.249
water cycle.

00:00:10.249 --> 00:00:11.868
First, the hot

00:00:11.868 --> 00:00:13.487
sun warms the

00:00:13.487 --> 00:00:15.105
water in oceans

00:00:15.105 --> 00:00:16.724
and lakes. The

00:00:16.724 --> 00:00:18.342
water turns into

00:00:18.342 --> 00:00:19.961
invisible steam and

00:00:19.961 --> 00:00:21.579
rises.

00:00:21.579 --> 00:00:23.079
High in the

00:00:23.079 --> 00:00:24.579
cold sky, this

00:00:24.579 --> 00:00:26.079
steam cools down

00:00:26.079 --> 00:00:27.579
and gathers together

00:00:27.579 --> 00:00:29.079
to form soft

00:00:29.079 --> 00:00:30.579
white clouds.

00:00:30.579 --> 00:00:31.992
When clouds get

00:00:31.992 --> 00:00:33.405
too heavy, they

00:00:33.405 --> 00:00:34.818
release the water

00:00:34.818 --> 00:00:36.231
as rain or

00:00:36.231 --> 00:00:37.644
snow, returning water

00:00:37.644 --> 00:00:39.057
back to the

00:00:39.057 --> 00:00:40.469
Earth.

